						<div class="postbody">I don't see any reason to pad ROMs for use on real HW unless game wants something from the area beyond ROM as pointed out before... if it works in emulator, it will do so on real HW, unless there's some bugs (in case of homebrew). Emulators don't usually emulate address wrapping and such... at least not MD emulators.</div>

					
